<HL>
   Gantos's August Sales Fell 2%
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   GTOS
</CO>
<IN>
SPECIALTY APPAREL RETAILERS (SAP)
</IN>
<LP>
   GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. -- Gantos Inc., a women's clothing
retailer, said its August sales fell 2% to $16.1 million from
$16.4 million a year earlier. Sales at stores open at least
one year dropped 18%.
   The year-earlier total included sales from Gantos's
semiannual boutique clearance sale, held this year in July.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the first eight months of this year, sales rose 15% to
$138.4 million from $120.3 million a year earlier.
</TEXT>
